text: The fact that people have mixed feelings is above what I expected. Nobody remembers that when Dumb and Dumber first came out in 1994 most people didn't care for it but now it's considered a great comedy. It's surprising how many "classics" were not loved or obsessively-quoted until a few months or years after its release.  The best part about this trailer is that it keeps the same era of comedy from the early 90s that the original had. It's not trying to be something new or "Judd Apatow-style." It feels like the original. Keep in mind the humor in the original was "silly" not "witty." The comedy was lowbrow but isn't that the stuff we've been laughing at for all of history? Farts are never disappointing.

text: I screened this movie, and I have to say that this trailer has all of the shock value funny in it. By that I mean, excluding a few "twists" most of the stand out moments are in this trailer. However.. the magic of DND is the in between and the chemistry of the 2 leads. Basically, when you watch this trailer you see a lot of the funny, most of it. But, the glue that binds is the rest of the film. In no way is this a shock movie, on the contrary the entire film, from score to set is basically a time capsule to the 90s, only taking place 20 years later. I rated this a B+/A- after screening, and that wasnt' because of the shocks you see here, it was because Jim and Jeff bring their A game and make all the parts between what you see here, glorious. Trailer gives a glimpse, go see it in the theater.
author: Mike Coulter

author: Athol Withers

text: Dumb and Dumber is by far my top favorite movie. When I first heard rumors of the sequel I couldn't of been more excited. When I saw the official announcement that they were working on it, it was even more of a thrill and such an anticipation. Looking at the trailer however has unfortunately gave me a sense of worries. The plot seems solid, but the bits and pieces seem less than what I would of thought or expected. I think I -just like many others- might just be comparing it to the original, which of course you can never duplicate an original, only thing you can do is make it as best as possible. It just seems like the sequal is more scripted and forceful than the first film. The original of course all characters fit like a glove and it feels like I'm watching the unscripted talents of 2 best friends naturally playing the role. Then again it might be a little absurd me going on a rant and jumping to conclusion on the sequal from a 2 and a half minute trailer. I know I'll be there at the midnight movie premier for this flick,  I just really hope it doesn't disappoint.

text: That scene at the end of the trailer is absolutely retarded.  I suspect the movie is going to be filled with this same kind of perverted humor, which was always a habit with the Farrelys, but they found the absolute perfect balance for it in the original, as well as in Kingpin, their other classic.  This looks like they're back to their Me, Myself, and Irene days, which isn't a good thing.   This one certainly doesn't have the same timeless and classic  feel to it as the original.  I didn't have my hopes up, because I know that lightning rarely strikes the same place twice, but I have less hope now after seeing this trailer.  I'll still see it, but I won't be expecting very much.

text: FIRST OF ALL!!! The grandma scene needs to be cut immediately. The cat's name needs to be changed IMMEDIATELY! Butthole? Seriously??? They go from Petey to Butthole? Wow... Lloyd isn't stupid enough to casually think he's talking to his dead dad. He traveled hundreds of miles and tracked down one girl successfully and now this? The phone scene needs a better script for sure. Also it's really stupid that Lloyd has a catheter or however it's spelled. And then for harry to tank it out like that? C'mon, I know he's dumb but he was never THAT dumb in the first movie. And the "THAT'S...AWESOME!" Line sounds so stupid. They're trying to recreate the "and totally redeem yourself!" gag from the first film but it isn't nearly as funny. This is probably the most negative comment on here but I've been waiting so long for this sequel because the original is my favorite comedy movie ever and my second favorite movie ever made. So this is really really disappointing to see. Of course you guys can't judge it by the trailer so I'm still excited. What people don't realize is the original trailer for the original dumb and dumber made the movie look horrible as well! Some scenes in that trailer were either completely different or completely removed from the final cut. So my hopes are still high that they will make some necessary changes to the editing.

text: People keep saying "Jim Carrey is not funny anymore." He's still very funny, he's just been in movies that don't help his comedic performance. I've always laughed at Jim in his comedic roles even when the movie isn't really that good (Popper's Penguins, Burt Wonderstone) Like Eddie Murphy, he's always been funny and in every movie he's been in he says stuff that will make you laugh or chuckle. Eddie just needs to get back to the raunchy or more mature comedies. Tower Heist reminded us that Eddie is needed most in those type of roles. I guess that's why he's making Beverly Hills Cop 4. Honestly, neither Jim nor Eddie need sequels to gain relevancy, they need strong original comedies, but I understand that sequels tend to be a boost in a lukewarm career. Jim will always be funny though and I can't wait to see this movie

text: If EVERYONE can stop comparing this to the original and stop saying a sequel should have never been made and see this movie as a stand alone movie as well as a movie to feed the curiosity of "i wonder what happened to those two dumb guys after chasing Mary and how are their lives now" then you can appreciate this movie. Dont look at it comparing to the original but its not trying to be better then the original. The original was ahead of its time and very different type of comedy and no other stupid comedy type movies topped it because it was the first that started the rest of that genre. This is just continuing their story and what happened 20 years later, giving us more of what we loved from these two. A continuation, almost like this is the rest of the original movie. Thankfully its the same production and actors. so stop saying they shouldnt have done a sequel or saying it wont top the original! Geez just enjoy more from these two.

It looks like two guys are trying to make some prank versions of Harry and Lloyd. So much over acting. I just hope that the movie is nothing like it. Seems like Daniels doesnt remember how to do comedy anymore, Harry ain't shouting and laughing all the time in the first movie but in this trailer it is all that he does. And I wont even say what I think about Carrey's lines. The original movie for me was all about the stupid little conversations, weird faces and hilarious but subtle road trip. Now its so off the top that it is embarrassing. There is a tiny chance that the trailer gives a wrong impression and the final movie will kick ass, but I doubt it considering the trash the directors have put out in last years.

text: I still hope it good.  But I think the biggest misstep might be, ironically, that they made the characters "dumb".  The first one was so good because each character had their odd moments of smartness that offset their dumbness.  In fact, most of the funniest jokes were because the criminals assumed that they two were competing criminal masterminds. Also, neither actor "played" dumb...the script made them dumb.  They were sort of blissfully unaware of their dumbness, and--on top of that--the rest of the characters were only marginally aware of Harry and Lloyd's true dumbness or they thought more along the lines of "they must be kidding, right?"...for instance, Marry Swanson had a genuinely good time with Harry.  The problem with this trailer, at least, is that the joke is on the characters as opposed to being on their circumstances.  But, just my opinion.

text: Looks stupid.  Saw the first one in theaters when it came out in 94 and many times thereafter on tape and it is a classic. It is hilarious.   But, I just don't care anymore. As the years go by and movies coming are are getting worse and worse, you start to realize, it's because the audience is getting more stupid.     It's the audience that determines how funny a movie will be these days. And people get "stupider" by the day, so that's the kind of humor they will pay to see. The humor that's just "random" or "silly" filled with cliché and trite jokes.       I blame the people who were born in 1990 or later. The benchmark of humor has been set by them using YouTube user-content as their standard.

The humor is also close to slapstick, and is kind of simple compared to the original. Really, 20 years in a home? Hand up grandma's pussy?  I am in no way prude (I love Seth Mcfarlane) but I feel like they ruined a classic, a movie that was fun for the whole family. However I speak from the trailer alone.

text: I just saw the movie just now and which.... They are even dumber in the sequel, not even kidding. The first movie it seemed like you always had to wait like 4 to 5 minutes for Harry and Lyod to do/say something dumb to make you laugh in the movie but, in the sequel it was like Lyod and Harry were just constantly acting dumb like every 2 to 3 seconds through the whole damn movie. No joke. There was hundreds of parts in this movie where they where constantly just acting dumb the whole time. There's so many of  those scenes in the movie to where I cant seem to even figure which scene made me laugh the most. There was too many times they act so dumb to where it started to feel like they were just trying to act dumb on purpose it was a little upsetting in a way I cant say the movie was all that perfect but, if you're fan of the old classic comedy that the first Dumb & Dumber movie had then your in for a surprise. It brought back good childhood memories to me cause I was very young when I saw the first film so I still accept it as a good comedy movie for its prime.

text: I worked on this film and was in several scenes as an extra and met jim carrey as well while on set, and after seeing the film I must say it was not as good as I thought it would be. The first dumb and dumber is such a masterpiece that I guess the bar is set really high for a sequel. It cant compare to the first one, it just didnt feel natural, perhaps because of age or the material, but the stupidity felt forced where the original was more natural and moved a lot better. If you just want to laugh I recommend seeing it, but definitely watch the original it is far greater and moves well. I can be seen on the back of the golf cart on the outside shot before they enter the auditorium.

text: 6/10. To all the haters, come on, it's a sequel. Honestly, sequels are never better than the original, you can't expect them to be. After reading the reviews on Amazon, I was hesitant on buying the movie because of the negativity, but I'm glad I have a mind of my own and bought it anyway. The movie really had some funny parts to it, especially when they find their old van and jump it like in the original, only to have it fall apart. The behind-the-scenes footage on the DVD was pretty cool, the sheep van was actually from the original movie; it had moss growing on it because it sat outside for the better part of 20 years. Not the best comedy of the year, but well worth watching. I'm glad they decided to make it after "Dumb and Dumberer" bombed so bad.

text: Do you know what I've noticed and didn't like about D&D2? Dumb and Dumber seemed to have an air of seriousness to it. Like Lloyd and Harry were dumb but it was in a subtle sort of way. Sure there was slapstick and stupidity but they had moments of seriousness which were still tinged with humor, like when Lloyd breaks down or when they're arguing on the freeway. This felt more like Dumb and Dumberer in the way of they ramped up their stupidity to fit more physical humor. I liked the film, but I felt it lacked the spirit of the first one.
